pageContext.claim: “'The Lisa Page (FBI) transcript also confirms earlier reporting that Page testified Russian Collusion was still unproven when Special Counsel Robert Mueller was appointed.' Catherine Herridge, @FoxNews  In other words they appointed someone when there was (and is) no crime. Bad!”
pageContext.analysis: Lisa Page texted extensively with Peter Strzok who expressed hesitation opening an investigation “because of [his] gut sense and concern there’s no big there there.” But the FBI did think there was reason to investigate and ultimately, the Mueller investigation is to determine if there is a "there there."
